00:19:25.830 --> 00:19:30.060
They don't own more than
1% of what they invest in.

00:19:30.060 --> 00:19:32.200
They have some political things.

00:19:32.200 --> 00:19:35.050
No bomb makers, I think
no cigarette maker,

00:19:35.050 --> 00:19:36.803
they're good, good.

00:19:37.656 --> 00:19:38.489
- [Harry] Good Scandinavian--

00:19:38.489 --> 00:19:39.580
- Good, good, good Norway.

00:19:39.580 --> 00:19:41.950
Now if all the investment
funds were like this,

00:19:41.950 --> 00:19:44.930
it'd be not at all,
certainly not even a problem,

00:19:44.930 --> 00:19:46.993
not even a question, they're not.

00:19:48.740 --> 00:19:52.563
You have a very large Russian,

00:19:54.490 --> 00:19:56.033
sovereign wealth fund.

00:19:57.836 --> 00:19:58.960
- [Harry] From oil also?

00:19:58.960 --> 00:20:00.679
- Yeah, yeah, from oil.

00:20:00.679 --> 00:20:03.120
Well, there are two sources of these.

00:20:03.120 --> 00:20:07.040
There's the mineral, the
oil which are a bunch

00:20:07.040 --> 00:20:10.220
of the Persian Gulf and oil countries,

00:20:10.220 --> 00:20:12.590
and Russia in a big way.

00:20:12.590 --> 00:20:14.890
And then there are the
Chinese manufacturers,

00:20:14.890 --> 00:20:18.243
the Asian manufacturers, exemplary China.

00:20:20.900 --> 00:20:25.900
Which has north of $2,000 billion dollars.

00:20:28.680 --> 00:20:30.120
- [Harry] In dollars?

00:20:30.120 --> 00:20:35.120
- Yeah, say about that, north
of two trillion in dollars

00:20:36.160 --> 00:20:38.000
sitting there in various tills.

00:20:38.000 --> 00:20:40.250
It's not necessarily
a sovereign world fund

00:20:40.250 --> 00:20:43.423
but under direct and
indirect government control.

00:20:45.690 --> 00:20:47.040
How do you use it?

00:20:47.040 --> 00:20:49.090
Well, if you were the Chinese government,

00:20:50.350 --> 00:20:52.820
you'd try and use it strategically.

00:20:52.820 --> 00:20:55.130
I mean one thing is you
just put it out there

00:20:55.130 --> 00:20:58.113
and earn a return and
people line for index funds.

00:21:01.791 --> 00:21:04.241
In others you say, well
our mission here on earth

00:21:05.360 --> 00:21:09.793
is to advance the Chinese economy.

00:21:10.640 --> 00:21:12.493
Well, we got this enormous tool here,

00:21:13.398 --> 00:21:14.290
what do we do with it?

00:21:14.290 --> 00:21:18.480
Well, what we need, we
could use some technology.

00:21:18.480 --> 00:21:19.980
Well, this may help us get it.

00:21:22.069 --> 00:21:24.370
And so we were raising
some of these questions.

00:21:24.370 --> 00:21:26.770
Ooh, come to think of it,
it might be political,

00:21:27.820 --> 00:21:31.460
if that President of the United
States, whatever his name is

00:21:31.460 --> 00:21:35.680
makes no difference, starts doing things

00:21:35.680 --> 00:21:40.543
that we don't like, that
hurt us, that irk us.

00:21:42.160 --> 00:21:45.670
What if the limousine that
brings the Chinese bankers

00:21:45.670 --> 00:21:50.160
to New York to buy the US
debt every Thursday morning,

00:21:50.160 --> 00:21:51.163
has a flat tire?

00:21:53.000 --> 00:21:54.770
In fact, what if we announced in advance

00:21:54.770 --> 00:21:58.343
we're going to have a
flat tire and not show?

00:21:59.290 --> 00:22:02.893
That might send the market
town a thousand points.

00:22:05.077 --> 00:22:10.030
That president, maybe
he has to think about us

00:22:10.030 --> 00:22:11.643
before opening his big mouth.

00:22:12.640 --> 00:22:16.930
This is a change, is this not a change?

00:22:16.930 --> 00:22:21.930
- So in essence, what came about

00:22:23.990 --> 00:22:26.950
as the sovereign funds
developed especially

00:22:26.950 --> 00:22:28.750
in the case of the Chinese,

00:22:28.750 --> 00:22:33.750
was really a change in the power balance

00:22:33.890 --> 00:22:37.273
between the two countries
beginning in the economic realm.

00:22:38.257 --> 00:22:43.010
And this is a major
unexpected disturbance,

00:22:43.010 --> 00:22:47.620
if you buy into what you
call the neoliberal view

00:22:47.620 --> 00:22:50.720
of the world, which was the doctrine,

00:22:50.720 --> 00:22:54.770
the policy that the
United States had embraced

00:22:56.340 --> 00:22:57.833
several decades ago.

00:22:59.540 --> 00:23:04.210
So the book moves toward a look,

00:23:04.210 --> 00:23:08.560
essentially it's the epitaph
of the neoliberal paradigm

00:23:08.560 --> 00:23:10.980
for domestic policy in the United States,

00:23:10.980 --> 00:23:15.980
because that policy produced
this very great disturbance

00:23:17.510 --> 00:23:19.280
which we'll talk about again in a minute,

00:23:19.280 --> 00:23:21.030
the sovereign funds.

00:23:21.030 --> 00:23:22.700
- Several other big disturbances.

00:23:22.700 --> 00:23:27.700
Yes, I think it has been
pretty unfortunate for America.

00:23:27.760 --> 00:23:32.760
- So what is the neoliberal paradigm?

00:23:33.480 --> 00:23:34.630
- That's really simple.

00:23:35.500 --> 00:23:36.650
Leave it to the market.

00:23:37.530 --> 00:23:42.110
Get the fat, stupid bureaucratic
hands of the state out.

00:23:42.110 --> 00:23:42.963
Deregulate.

00:23:44.920 --> 00:23:45.923
And play this out.

00:23:46.850 --> 00:23:49.383
And everything will spin
around and work out fine.

00:23:50.700 --> 00:23:53.566
Now, there are a lot
of problems with this,

00:23:53.566 --> 00:23:57.300
sometimes it doesn't, that's
called macroeconomics gains.

00:23:57.300 --> 00:23:59.803
But also, what if the other
guys are not doing it?

00:24:01.190 --> 00:24:03.410
They may even make-believe,
which I don't believe

00:24:03.410 --> 00:24:05.310
for a minute that this
is the best way to do it

00:24:05.310 --> 00:24:06.283
for a country.

00:24:07.700 --> 00:24:08.983
But what about the other countries?

00:24:10.160 --> 00:24:13.360
So if you were playing touch football,

00:24:13.360 --> 00:24:15.623
and the other guy's got a
helmet and shoulder pads,

00:24:17.190 --> 00:24:18.690
maybe this is not a good idea.

00:24:22.800 --> 00:24:26.350
There is a strategic element
and that's sometimes absent

00:24:26.350 --> 00:24:27.393
in such thinking.

00:24:32.110 --> 00:24:34.823
A whole bunch of things came together.

